        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down, Beckenham, | Kent.</placeName>
                    <date>June 25th, 1869.</date>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I have read several of Mr. E. Ray Lankester’s papers in various Journals, and have been struck by the ability and knowledge shown in them, and by his zeal for Science. Therefore in my opinion he would be well-qualified for giving Lectures on Biology, and for leading students along the right path.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>Charles Darwin.</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Lankester was a candidate for the Lee’s Readership in anatomy at Christ Church, Oxford; he was unsuccessful (see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_4710.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Lester 1995</ref>, pp. 22–3). No letter from Lankester requesting a recommendation has been found.</note>
        </div>        
            
